description:
Gay Pride commemorates the Stonewall riots, which began in June 28, 1969, after police raided the Stonewall Inn bar in New York;

The early demonstrations often focused simply on participants’ being proud to be out of the closet, on individual freedom, and on the diversity of the LGBTQ community. But since the 1980s, political and social activism has become central to the events of Pride.

Every battle has marked our faces, but at least now we can see the rainbow <3
